    <abstract><!-- can be changed via merge in the assembly -->
      <para>Enable network connection to access and connect devices and resources.</para>
      </abstract>
  </info><section>
<title>Enabling network connection</title>
  <para>Activate network connections using the <command>nmcli</command> command.</para>
  <procedure xml:id="enable-networkmanager"><step><para>View the list of existing connections:</para>
  <screen>nmcli connection show</screen>
  <para>The active network connections appear with the names and UUIDs.</para>
  </step>
  <step><para>Enable a connection using the name or UUID:</para>
  <screen>nmcli connection up uuid <replaceable>CONNECTION-UUID</replaceable></screen></step>
  <step><para>If networking is disabled using <command>nmcli networking off</command> command, enable networking:</para>
  <screen>nmcli networking on</screen></step>
  <step><para>View the connection status:</para>
  <screen>nmcli connection show --active</screen></step>
  <step><para>Enable a Wi-Fi network connection:</para>
  <screen>nmcli device wifi connect <replaceable>SSID</replaceable> password <replaceable>PASSWORD</replaceable></screen></step>
</procedure></section>
<section>
<title>Disabling network connection</title>
  <para>You can temporarily disconnect your system from external
  networks using the <command>nmcli</command> command to
  disable your network connection.</para>
  <procedure xml:id="disable-networkmanager"><step><para>View the list of active connections:</para>
  <screen>nmcli connection show --active</screen>
  <para>The active network connections appear with the names and UUIDs.</para>
  </step>
  <step><para>Terminate a specific connection:</para>
  <screen>nmcli connection down <replaceable>CONNECTION-NAME/CONNECTION-UUID</replaceable></screen>
  </step>
  <step><para>Disable network connection:</para>
  <screen>nmcli networking off</screen>
  </step>
 </procedure></section>
</topic>